  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - This proposal CONSTITUTES DEVELOPMENT within the meaning of Section 55 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990, and a planning application IS REQUIRED. \r\nThe proposed side extension would extend beyond a wall which fronts a highway and forms a side elevation of the original dwellinghouse and would thereby fail to comply with Class A. A.1 (e) (ii) of Schedule 2, Part 1, of the Town & Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015. Planning permission would therefore be required.\r\n",
    "Reason : 2 - This proposal CONSTITUTES DEVELOPMENT within the meaning of Section 55 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990, and a planning application IS REQUIRED. \r\nThe proposed front porch would be within 2 metres of the boundary of the curtilage of the dwellinghouse with a highway and would thereby fail to comply with Class D. D.1 (d) of Schedule 2, Part 1, of the Town & Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015. Planning permission would therefore be required.\r\n"
